My shot is that your `WebConfig` is [not placed in the right package](https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/current/reference/html/using-spring-boot.html#using-boot-structuring-your-code).
If your `@SpringBootApplication` annotated class is in `com.example.demo`
then your `WebConfig` class should be placed under the `com.example.demo` package (or other sub-package, e.g: `com.example.demo.config`).
```java
package com.example.demo.config; // &lt;-- move it to the (not-default) package

// skipped imports
// ...

@Configuration
@EnableWebSecurity
@EnableGlobalMethodSecurity(prePostEnabled = true)
public class WebConfig extends WebSecurityConfigurerAdapter {

    @Override
    protected void configure(HttpSecurity http) throws Exception {
      // config same as in the question&#39;s snippet
      // ...
    }
}
```

